25|$|Harlow wrote a novel {{entitled}} Today is Tonight. In Arthur Landau's {{introduction to}} the 1965 paperback edition, Harlow stated her intention <b>to</b> <b>write</b> <b>the</b> <b>book</b> around 1933–34 {{but it was not}} published during her lifetime. After her death, Landau writes, her mother sold the film rights to MGM, though no film was made. The publication rights were passed from Harlow's mother to a family friend and the book was finally published in 1965.|$|E
