50|$|During the Second World War Piggott {{worked as}} an air photo interpreter. He was posted to India, where he spent time {{studying}} the archaeology of the sub-continent, eventually leading him <b>to</b> <b>write</b> <b>the</b> <b>books</b> Some Ancient Cities of India (1946) and Prehistoric India (1950). These experiences provided him with a valuable external view of European prehistory, which was to prove useful on his return to Britain.|$|R
